          <title>Blackhawks' rally falls short in season-opening 5-2 loss in Utah</title>
          <description><![CDATA[SALT LAKE CITY (AP) — The Utah Hockey Club got off to a great start in its new hometown Tuesday night. The Blackhawks' start, meanwhile, was less than ideal. Utah never trailed in a season opener, building a 3-0 lead before holding off a Chicago rally for a 5-2 victory.]]></description>
